till best to user test any important set of interaction controls."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{"id":"always-offer-a-default-selection"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#always-offer-a-default-selection","ariaLabel":"always offer a default selection permalink","className":["anchor"]},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"svg","properties":{"height":"16","width":"16","fill":"#0000ff","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","viewBox":"0 0 32 32"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"defs","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"style","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":".cls-1{fill:none;}"}]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"title","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"icons"}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"g","properties":{"id":"Icon"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M29.2416,6.7587a6.0194,6.0194,0,0,0-8.5039,0l1.4172,1.4171a4.0089,4.0089,0,0,1,5.67,5.6694l-7.9793,7.9791a4.0089,4.0089,0,0,1-5.67-5.6694l1.4176-1.4171L14.176,13.3206l-1.4176,1.4171a6.0131,6.0131,0,0,0,8.5039,8.5036l7.9793-7.9791A6.02,6.02,0,0,0,29.2416,6.7587Z"},"children":[]},{"type":"element","tagName":"path","properties":{"d":"M4.1783,24.8217a4.0164,4.0164,0,0,1,0-5.6738l7.9688-7.9672a4.0121,4.0121,0,1,1,5.6746,5.6734l-2.12,2.1195L17.12,20.3918l2.12-2.1195a6.0179,6.0179,0,0,0-8.5114-8.51L2.76,17.73a6.0181,6.0181,0,0,0,8.5114,8.51L9.8529,24.8217A4.0177,4.0177,0,0,1,4.1783,24.8217Z"},"children":[]}]},{"type":"element","tagName":"g","properties":{"id":"Transparent_Rectangle","dataName":"Transparent Rectangle"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"rect","properties":{"className":["cls-1"],"x":"-0.0116","y":"-0.0007","width":"32","height":"32"},"children":[]}]}]}]},{"type":"text","value":"Always Offer a Default Selection"}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"One of the 10 heuristics of UI design says that users should be able to undo (and redo) their actions. This means enabling people to set a UI control back to its original state. In case of radio buttons this means that radio buttons should always have exactly one option pre-selected. Select the safest (to prevent loss of data or system access) and most secure and private option. If safety and security aren’t factors, select the most likely or convenient option."}]},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If users might need to refrain from making a selection, you should provide a radio button for this choice, such as one labeled “None.” Offering users an explicit, neutral option to click is much better than requiring the implicit act of not selecting from the list."}]}],"data":{"quirksMode":false}},"fields":{"slug":"/components/radio/","path":"/components/radio/","currentPage":"radio","sourcePath":"docs/components/radio.md"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Radio","label":"Component"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"frontmatter":{"title":"Radio","label":"Component"}}}